						<summary>

						<p>On a hero-stone in front of the Rāmaliṅga temple.</p>						

						<p>1106 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the Chalukya Vikrama year 31, Vyaya, Śrāvaṇa śu. Thursday. If the lost <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> is <hi rend="italic">daśami,</hi> the details correspond to 1106 A.D., July 12.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record the death of Chāvagāvuṇḍa and Holligāvuṇḍa in a fight against the forces of Chāgaladēvī, wife of a chief of Toṟagale.</p>						

						</summary>
